column11: Framework contract to implement a programme for paper and/or electronic publications on European employment, social affairs and equal opportunities policy.
column12: The aim of the framework contract is to assist the Employment, Social Affairs and Equal Opportunities DG in implementing its programme of publications. As the Office for Official Publications of the European Communities takes responsibility for most of the printing work, the assistance required will mainly involve tasks to be carried out prior to printing, namely, writing and rewriting of texts, translation and graphic design, amongst others. The contract will take the form of a framework contract, as the exact quantities involved and the dates on which the various services in the contract are to be provided cannot be precisely established. Due to the synergies between the various tasks to be performed, the framework contract will not be divided into lots.
